replies.body:
I'm sorry to hear about your panic attacks.  Some of the people closest to me have generalized anxiety disorder, and it's so scary to watch, I can't imagine what it's like to live through one.  I hope you've found something you enjoy better for your nights.

Do I think it's your fault?  Let me put it this way.  Let's say you weep uncontrollably every time you watch violence against the animal in a traditional Spanish bullfight.  That's completely reasonable: those are brutal, bloody, generally one-sided affairs, I would never watch one myself.  I don't think there's anything wrong with you for breaking down at the thought of it.  That said, if you go to watch a bullfight, and the 9 people sitting nearest to you in the arena (surely machismo-obsessed sociopaths: they enjoy this spectacle) feel like they've wasted half an hour because your grief is so distracting.  Well, in that case, those sociopaths have the right to be upset, because they committed their time to this activity: and you should consider not going to any more bullfights, because it usually doesn't go well for the bull.

